Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.34,0:00:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We're producing this videotape informally out at the ranch.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.94,0:00:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a studio production.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.57,0:00:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose is to merely illustrate the main points that we make in the book Power vs. Force.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.07,0:00:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to illustrate the technique of kinesiology, something about theory,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.45,0:00:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,something about its application in a great many different areas of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.61,0:00:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So this first videotape is a broad, general overview of the subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.92,0:00:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And not in-depth on any one particular thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.24,0:00:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Those will be separate videotapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.21,0:01:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the general overview, and as you'll see from the menu, which we'll follow shortly,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.47,0:01:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to touch briefly on a lot of subjects.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.65,0:01:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The one we're going to explore most, of course, is consciousness itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.51,0:01:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's what the whole book is about.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.79,0:01:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, I thought I'd just show you the basic technique of kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.60,0:01:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.65,0:01:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to take theory to a different section.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.59,0:01:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And the various subjects we're going to cover section by section.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.45,0:01:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But first is the basic technique itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.34,0:02:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very, very simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.23,0:02:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You ask the person to hold out their arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.70,0:02:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I usually use two fingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.73,0:02:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,First, I want to know their relative strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.21,0:02:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.16,0:02:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I always say resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.53,0:02:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.33,0:02:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, now to make sure this is a suitable subject,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.83,0:02:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I ask the person to picture someone they love.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.36,0:02:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Close your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.71,0:02:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Picture someone you love and resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.18,0:02:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.21,0:02:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now picture some horrible event in your life or somebody you don't love.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.53,0:02:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.31,0:02:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Picture Adolf Hitler.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.69,0:02:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.03,0:02:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, a normal subject goes strong with love and goes weak with hate or fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.93,0:02:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Or a normal subject goes, hold, hold it here, I'm licking it in mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.53,0:02:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.43,0:02:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.24,0:02:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold Adolf Hitler in mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.53,0:02:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.65,0:03:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, a normal subject goes positive with positive stimuli.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.00,0:03:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And goes weak with negative stimuli.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.50,0:03:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This is very, very important to first test the subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.08,0:03:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There are 2.4% of the population will give you the opposite effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.11,0:03:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is a whole subject in itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.61,0:03:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,These are people whose acupuncture system is totally blown out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.25,0:03:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Their thymus gland is totally blown out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.30,0:03:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Occasionally, a normal person will give you a paradoxical response.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.06,0:03:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The way you cure that was figured out by Dr. John Diamond.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.87,0:03:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The negative, the paradoxical response, that is, something positive makes you go weak,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.80,0:03:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is due to an underactivity of the thymus gland, the immune suppression.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.90,0:03:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you get a normal person who's leading a normal life,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.71,0:03:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,who's not into criminality and negativity and heavy metal rock and drugs and stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.34,0:04:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and they give you a paradoxical response,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.52,0:04:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you can use what John Diamond, the Dr. Diamond, called the thymic thump.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.41,0:04:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You go, thymus gland is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.97,0:04:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,here it's the central organ of the immune system so if a person who's
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.25,0:04:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,normal gives you a paradoxical response you smile think of someone you love and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.20,0:04:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you thump over the thymus gland rhythmically three times you like this
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.38,0:04:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha now when you retest the person they will go normal
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.63,0:04:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,except for 2.4 percent of population who won't go normal anyway all right so
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.69,0:04:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,first we make sure we have a normal test subject next we don't have any
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.63,0:04:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,extraneous extraneous stimuli in other words it's very important not to have
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.89,0:04:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,music in the background it's best to be to get for accurate results you should
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.75,0:04:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,be impersonal try not to radiate love and affection and laughter and that kind
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.62,0:05:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of thing because you don't want to get false positives you can have the subject
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.23,0:05:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,close their eyes because what they're looking at might have an effect like
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.97,0:05:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,anything else
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.67,0:05:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.06,0:05:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,just takes a little experimentation when you're learning archery how to run a
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.38,0:05:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,video camera or what just takes a little experience it's a very very reliable
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.06,0:05:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,technique as we've said elsewhere in these tapes it's been used by tens of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.05,0:05:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,thousands of practitioners for over 20 years all around the globe all kinds of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.56,0:05:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,physicians and our neurologists and nutritionists physicians of all kinds
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.36,0:05:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,chiropractors it's extremely accurate
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.94,0:05:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the only difference is the way it's been used up until the research I did was
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.25,0:05:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,mainly for material things and strictly physical phenomena and I'm really took
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.68,0:05:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,it out to different dimensions so that's the technique and will demonstrate it in
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.86,0:06:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,a variety of subjects okay well you're like a little radio and we're gonna get
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.77,0:06:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you to cut in and tell us what's playing in the field of consciousness so let's
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.07,0:06:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,see you like these did you have some of those before no this switch is on now
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.93,0:06:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see you like these did you have some of those before no this switch is on now
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.52,0:06:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see you like these did you have some of those before no this switch is on now
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.68,0:06:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. First, we're going to just check this out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.45,0:06:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Put your arm out. Now resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.62,0:06:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Now hold somebody you love in, hold your mom in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.20,0:06:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.51,0:06:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold somebody you don't like in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.36,0:06:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You got somebody you don't like?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.94,0:06:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody you're scared of?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.91,0:06:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.77,0:06:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,She goes weak. She really goes weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.19,0:06:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. You like those, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.07,0:06:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you like them because you're eating them up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.69,0:06:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You're eating them up for...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.06,0:06:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Look at the curtain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.56,0:06:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy of these is positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.67,0:06:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.67,0:06:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, all these will be sort of positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.11,0:07:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy of what's in this is positive. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.54,0:07:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You're pretty strong when something goes positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.69,0:07:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,No, she never does.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.75,0:07:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You can look at it if you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.37,0:07:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Just look at this guy and hold him in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.73,0:07:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Now resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.06,0:07:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold him. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.14,0:07:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. His energy is positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.61,0:07:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's Mr. Deutsch, who's head of the CIA.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.50,0:07:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.06,0:07:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That's very good news. Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.16,0:07:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Here's a newspaper. It's got somebody's picture in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.54,0:07:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This man has positive energy. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.27,0:07:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This man has a negative energy. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.06,0:07:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the positive energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.56,0:07:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,This man's energy calibrates over 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.27,0:07:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.49,0:08:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,560.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.18,0:08:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,570.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.93,0:08:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This man's energy calibrates over 560.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.22,0:08:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you study about him in school?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.51,0:08:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what that is?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.62,0:08:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Abraham Lincoln.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.07,0:08:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Abraham Lincoln.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.95,0:08:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Abraham Lincoln.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.04,0:08:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's those nasty things?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.63,0:08:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, here they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.22,0:08:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold those over your solar plexus.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.83,0:08:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy of this product is positive. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.72,0:08:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You think you're going to smoke them?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.13,0:08:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.63,0:08:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,They make you go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.96,0:08:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They make you go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.20,0:08:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Who wants to smoke something that's going to make you go weak?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.20,0:08:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, here's something interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.72,0:08:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you ever see these before?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.47,0:08:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.86,0:08:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Let's just say
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.05,0:08:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy of what you...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.51,0:08:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You can look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.17,0:08:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy of what you're looking at is positive. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.70,0:08:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.70,0:08:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,She went weak but manufactured tobacco.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.34,0:08:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the kind of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.79,0:08:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this was grown organically.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.22,0:09:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm trying to demonstrate here with this tobacco
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.25,0:09:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the response is not only the opposite
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.20,0:09:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of what the individual believes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.82,0:09:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The response is the opposite of what everybody believes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.14,0:09:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody thinks that this causes cancer and yet you went positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.59,0:09:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what we are merely demonstrating is
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.89,0:09:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that the answer will be the same no matter what a person's belief system is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.72,0:09:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I've tested this a lot of times
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.12,0:09:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and a group of 20 people all convinced
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.87,0:09:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that tobacco causes cancer
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.48,0:09:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet when I hold this organic,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.27,0:09:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,hold that over your tummy,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.20,0:09:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy of this is positive. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.20,0:09:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy of this is negative. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.64,0:10:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So, despite the fact that everybody has a very strong,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.79,0:10:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,reinforced belief system,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.79,0:10:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the answer we got was exactly the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.79,0:10:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what we're demonstrating then is
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.08,0:10:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the impersonality of this response.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.48,0:10:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a letter I wrote about some guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.17,0:10:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't even know his name.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.78,0:10:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We came to a meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.78,0:10:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This man's energy is positive. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.84,0:10:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This man's energy is negative. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.94,0:10:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.94,0:10:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,See, we get the same answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.94,0:10:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,She doesn't know anything about any of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.94,0:10:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,She doesn't know any of the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.94,0:10:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just as valid in kids as it is in adults.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.20,0:10:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And, again, what we're testing
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.51,0:10:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is the capacity of this field
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.51,0:10:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to detect the differences between truth and falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.37,0:10:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll add something that I wrote about in the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.27,0:11:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,To become acquainted with the contents of this book here,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.51,0:11:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to become familiar with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.88,0:11:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to become familiar with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.10,0:11:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to read that book and sort of get it,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.10,0:11:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,raises a person's level of consciousness. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.20,0:11:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It raises it over 20 points. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.58,0:11:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,30 points. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.67,0:11:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,35 points. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.67,0:11:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,37 points. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.67,0:11:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the interesting thing is,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.22,0:11:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody who's ever heard the lectures or read the book,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.22,0:11:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,their own level of consciousness jumps 35 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.22,0:11:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in the average lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.99,0:11:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the average person on the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.99,0:11:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,during their lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.27,0:11:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,their level of consciousness advances over 5 points. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.27,0:11:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Does not.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.44,0:11:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It advances over 4 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.44,0:11:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,5 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.44,0:11:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,6 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.75,0:11:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The average person's level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.75,0:11:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,advances exactly 5 points in one lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.46,0:12:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And, therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.96,0:12:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,merely to become familiar with the truth about consciousness itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.96,0:12:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,seems to jump a person's own level of consciousness 35 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.22,0:12:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to read the book,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.22,0:12:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,by the time you finish the book,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.22,0:12:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you won't be the same person who started the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.08,0:12:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And the second time you read the book,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.08,0:12:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you will be a person of more advanced consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.08,0:12:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and the book will make a lot more sense the second time through.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.08,0:12:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd just take something out of the current news.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.08,0:12:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to start with archaeology.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.08,0:12:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Start with archaeology,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.24,0:12:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,because it just so happened that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.69,0:12:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,on TV the other night, I think it was Channel 8,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.69,0:12:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,was a whole program on Atlantis.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.08,0:12:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Archaeologic research.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.84,0:12:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Plato, 2300 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.84,0:12:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,wrote about the lost continent of Atlantis.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.84,0:12:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, he said that Atlantis existed 9,000 years before.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.36,0:13:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,However, we feel,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.58,0:13:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,or the program brought up,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.58,0:13:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that he's probably off one decimal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.58,0:13:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It was probably 900 years before, not 9,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.87,0:13:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Differences of one decimal
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.87,0:13:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,occur like in Britain and the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.87,0:13:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a difference of one decimal
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.87,0:13:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,as to what constitutes a billion.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.00,0:13:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.00,0:13:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The program brought this up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.19,0:13:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Atlantis exist 9,000 or 900 years before Plato?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.19,0:13:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's just ask that question.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.57,0:13:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,On the program it asked,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.57,0:13:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll ask now,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.24,0:13:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Plato was correct in stating that Atlantis existed 9,000 years
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.24,0:13:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,prior to his existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.24,0:13:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,More accurately,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.70,0:13:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a difference of a decimal there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.08,0:13:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What he meant in our use of numerology
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.17,0:13:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,was 900 years before this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.30,0:13:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.69,0:14:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the program brought up various places Atlantis could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.69,0:14:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's ask these questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.91,0:14:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Atlantis is located under Antarctica, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.97,0:14:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Atlantis is located near Bimini, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.00,0:14:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did they say it was?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.12,0:14:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,They said it was more likely located in the Aegean Sea, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.51,0:14:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That's interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.12,0:14:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what they said probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.52,0:14:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Near the island of Thera, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.80,0:14:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it the same as the old city of Akroteria?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.80,0:14:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Akroteria, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.37,0:14:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.37,0:14:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.08,0:14:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So this suggests that archaeologically Atlantis existed in the Aegean Sea
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.08,0:14:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,because it was outside the streets of Gibraltar.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.08,0:14:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But it doesn't say from what direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.14,0:15:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's another interesting thing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.72,0:15:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This week's newspaper says,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.72,0:15:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddha's birthplace found in Nepal, archaeologists say.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.36,0:15:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a correct location, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.75,0:15:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This is actually the Buddha's birthplace, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.50,0:15:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.54,0:15:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll notice that I don't ask questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.96,0:15:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I make a statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.96,0:15:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So in using the technique,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.96,0:15:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we always make a statement, a positive statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.96,0:15:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the inaccuracies that people write me
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.42,0:15:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that they're not getting accurate results
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.42,0:15:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,are due to the fact that they ask questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.42,0:15:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very easy to lapse into asking a question,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.51,0:15:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,like, is this the correct place for the Buddha's birthplace,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.74,0:15:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of just making a statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.74,0:16:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the archaeologic applications, of course, are endless.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.50,0:16:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And this film has to be of a certain limited length,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.50,0:16:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,so we could spend one entire videotape
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.83,0:16:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,just checking out archaeology
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.83,0:16:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and primitive drawings and caves
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.69,0:16:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and the ancient caves
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.69,0:16:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in France.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.36,0:16:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can go back into paleontology
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.36,0:16:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and track down, you know, the various artifacts
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.46,0:16:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and date them as their exact age
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.46,0:16:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of the various skulls
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.46,0:16:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and things that have been found in Africa and elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.12,0:16:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So the archaeologic applications are pretty endless.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.61,0:16:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go on to art.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.61,0:16:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have some interesting current things
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.82,0:16:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,having to do with art.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.36,0:16:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.38,0:16:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in a recent Time magazine here,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.38,0:17:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,we have a new Cupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.48,0:17:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And is it really a Michelangelo?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.79,0:17:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.86,0:17:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So here is a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.86,0:17:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That Cupid is actually a Michelangelo.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.01,0:17:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.59,0:17:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not a Michelangelo.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.35,0:17:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Here is a piece of original art.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.68,0:17:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Want to hold that over here so it reflects this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.36,0:17:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a genuine piece of art.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.03,0:17:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a genuine Salvador Dali resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.03,0:17:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the signature here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.01,0:17:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That is actually Dali's signature resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.20,0:17:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good to know,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.20,0:17:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,because when you invest in art,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.20,0:18:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,you're often talking about very large amounts of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.01,0:18:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a genuine piece of art resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.36,0:18:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.40,0:18:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,This is authentic resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.91,0:18:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.92,0:18:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the name here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.92,0:18:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Picasso.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.92,0:18:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.55,0:18:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.55,0:18:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a genuine autograph resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.61,0:18:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.61,0:18:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We can ask the question now in reverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.61,0:18:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This is actually a very clever fake resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.61,0:18:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.28,0:18:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're investing several million dollars,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.93,0:18:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,it's really good to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.93,0:18:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There are three paintings at the National Museum of Washington right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.07,0:18:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the authenticity of which is being disputed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.07,0:18:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So using this technique here,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.98,0:18:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,as you can see,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.98,0:18:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you could arrive at an answer rather quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.65,0:18:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought some applications in business might be useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.22,0:18:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It might be very interesting to just briefly run through.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.22,0:18:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.22,0:18:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,each one of these could take us all afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.92,0:19:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's an interesting business application
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.11,0:19:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that is very practical.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.11,0:19:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a few checks I got in the mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.44,0:19:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold that over your solar plexus.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.35,0:19:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a good check, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.58,0:19:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.58,0:19:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,it was rejected,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.58,0:19:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,lack of sufficient funds.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.80,0:19:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.27,0:19:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a proposition asking me
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.27,0:19:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to accept a transfer of $320,000 from Nigeria.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.68,0:19:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a legitimate business proposition, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.68,0:19:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a criminal enterprise, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.60,0:19:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a criminal enterprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.40,0:19:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It just so happened that there was a TV program about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.55,0:19:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,In Nigeria,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.55,0:19:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,there's some peculiarity of the corporate
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.55,0:20:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and business laws
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.55,0:20:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that allows them to do this kind of thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.91,0:20:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and they apparently have made a lot of money
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.39,0:20:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,on a lot of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.39,0:20:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought we would ask something.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.01,0:20:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just ask,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.01,0:20:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the integrity of this publisher, resist?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.04,0:20:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's good to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.61,0:20:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Veritas Publishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.61,0:20:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So before you invest in something,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.75,0:20:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,a stock, a bond,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.75,0:20:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,before you use a certain investment counselor,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.79,0:20:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you can check out the integrity of that particular enterprise,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.79,0:20:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that broker,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.79,0:20:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,or that stock.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.79,0:20:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I bought for the first time
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.04,0:20:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,some mutual fund,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.36,0:20:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,some mutual funds.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.09,0:20:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see, what was the name of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.42,0:20:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.68,0:21:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,This is an integrates fund, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.29,0:21:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.29,0:21:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so what I just,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.51,0:21:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,what I want to demonstrate is that the response
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.51,0:21:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't have anything to do with my verbalizing the thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.51,0:21:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with my holding it within consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.51,0:21:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have to tell you the name out loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.22,0:21:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I can keep it in my mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.38,0:21:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll get to the reason for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.64,0:21:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That brings us to the subject of consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.17,0:21:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Some explanation is necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.04,0:21:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We said that consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.03,0:21:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,we calibrated here the levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.03,0:21:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We could zoom in on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.83,0:21:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And on page 52 of the book,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.83,0:21:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,this map appears.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.94,0:21:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to show you that we can recapitulate this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.16,0:21:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,These are actually,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.16,0:22:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you see, consciousness is like a potential energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.16,0:22:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and within it are so-called levels,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.19,0:22:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,which we call attractor,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.41,0:22:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,attractor fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.41,0:22:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That comes out of nonlinear dynamics and chaos theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.35,0:22:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll get more into that in the section where we talk about theory,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.35,0:22:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but what chaos theory discovered was
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.20,0:22:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that behind what appears like random data,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.54,0:22:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is actually an organizing pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.70,0:22:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The most random data I can think of
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.70,0:22:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is the entire field of human consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.10,0:22:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look at the human dialogue throughout history,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.10,0:22:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,or through the current newspaper,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.10,0:22:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,or the news broadcast,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.24,0:22:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it looks totally chaotic.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.55,0:22:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All kinds of bizarre things happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.55,0:22:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,There seems to be no rhyme or reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.55,0:23:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Human behavior doesn't really make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.23,0:23:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody says they're going to be here at 1230.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.31,0:23:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's now quarter one, and they aren't here yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.31,0:23:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.31,0:23:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears chaotic.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.31,0:23:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But behind it, there are organizing patterns.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.50,0:23:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So one of the main things we did in the book was
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.50,0:23:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,provide some kind of a map of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.50,0:23:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and we used kinesiology to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.92,0:23:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason we used kinesiology to do it
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.92,0:23:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is because consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.10,0:23:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,has no dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.31,0:23:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness itself...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.57,0:23:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, in quantum theory,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.57,0:23:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,when you go beyond the smallest particle
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.57,0:23:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and the smallest energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.57,0:23:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you go beyond locality,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.67,0:23:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore you're beyond space
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.67,0:23:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're beyond time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.67,0:23:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So anything that happens within consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.67,0:23:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,is, you might say, recorded there forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.81,0:24:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So that means that we could recapitulate these levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.03,0:24:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.03,0:24:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's on page 52 of the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.58,0:24:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just stand back and let him zoom in a little bit on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.58,0:24:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The critical level is courage at 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.80,0:24:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.80,0:24:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's say...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.80,0:24:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say pride is over 200. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.71,0:24:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.76,0:24:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Pride is over 170. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.83,0:24:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Pride is about 175. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.83,0:24:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Pride is over 176. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.96,0:24:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright. Pride is about 175.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.08,0:24:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Anger is over 125.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.08,0:24:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,140.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.48,0:24:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,145.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.48,0:24:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,150.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.48,0:24:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll do it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.30,0:24:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Anger is over 149.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.30,0:24:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,150.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.14,0:24:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Anger is about 150.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.97,0:24:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.97,0:24:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Fear is over 90.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.06,0:24:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,98.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.25,0:24:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,99.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.25,0:24:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,100.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.45,0:25:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Fear is about 100.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.45,0:25:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can recapitulate all these levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.34,0:25:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything below 200 makes you go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.34,0:25:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Pride, anger, desire, fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.34,0:25:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,grief,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.34,0:25:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,apathy,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.34,0:25:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,guilt,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.34,0:25:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.75,0:25:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And all the variations of those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.75,0:25:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything from 200 up makes you go strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.24,0:25:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.43,0:25:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.92,0:25:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,250 is neutral. Let's ask that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.07,0:25:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,At neutral...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.47,0:25:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Neutral is...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.47,0:25:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay if it's this way and it's okay if it's that way. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.47,0:25:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,See, that's a positive feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.88,0:25:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Neutral.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.88,0:25:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If I get the job, it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.88,0:25:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I don't, I'll get another job. See?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.88,0:25:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're at anger, you're angry because you didn't get the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.10,0:25:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're in pride, you're arrogant about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.10,0:25:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're in fear, you're too fearful to pass the interview.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.17,0:25:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're in grief, you didn't get the job, so you're going to kill yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.17,0:25:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Apathy is...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.17,0:26:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's hopeless. There's no jobs around.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.17,0:26:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Shame is, well, I don't have a job, so I'm ashamed to be seen in public, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.96,0:26:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, neutral is okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.96,0:26:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Willing is something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.96,0:26:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Willing is around 310. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.96,0:26:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Reason is around 400. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.50,0:26:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Science is about 400. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.50,0:26:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.89,0:26:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we don't have Reason on?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.98,0:26:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah, we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.98,0:26:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Love starts at 500 and goes on up to 1,000. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.98,0:26:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Unconditional love is about 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.29,0:26:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Joy is about 580.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.61,0:26:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace of God is about...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.61,0:26:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace is what? 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.61,0:26:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Enlightenment is 600 to 1,000. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.35,0:26:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, let's check on kinesiology itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.54,0:26:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy level of kinesiology itself as a technique is approximately 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.57,0:26:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,500. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.57,0:26:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.02,0:26:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The level of truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.02,0:26:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never asked this before.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.02,0:27:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The level of truth of this map of consciousness here calibrates over 500. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.16,0:27:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 600. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.16,0:27:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 700. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.16,0:27:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 800. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.16,0:27:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 900. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.69,0:27:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The arm okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.69,0:27:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates about 840. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.84,0:27:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh, that's interesting. That's the level of...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.28,0:27:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the level of the book, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.98,0:27:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the level of the consciousness of this book.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.32,0:27:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over 700, 800, 840, 850.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.35,0:27:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the level of consciousness of the book itself, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.88,0:27:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, now, the consciousness has no dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.68,0:27:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's beyond space and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.31,0:27:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And the reason it works, kinesiology works, is it has to do with causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.30,0:27:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to have to get into causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.30,0:28:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to get into that more later.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.03,0:28:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What the world thinks is that causality moves from A to B to C.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.71,0:28:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In this direction, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.96,0:28:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, causality does not move that way at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.96,0:28:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It moves from consciousness into the world as ABC.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.01,0:28:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So causality does not work horizontally in this direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.01,0:28:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It works in this direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.24,0:28:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Something that's held in consciousness, then it manifests in the visible world.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.24,0:28:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me show you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.95,0:28:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a flower unfolding like that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.65,0:28:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.03,0:28:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This precedes this and is a necessary condition to reach this.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.03,0:28:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But this does not cause that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.20,0:28:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So what the world thinks when it sees ABC sequence,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.38,0:29:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,what it thinks is causality is not causality, it's a condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.85,0:29:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The condition for B to appear is preceded by A, but it is not caused by A.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.85,0:29:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we have a flower growing, then a bigger flower growing,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.96,0:29:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and then a bigger flower growing,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.21,0:29:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the smaller flower does not cause the bigger flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.21,0:29:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's the full-grown flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.21,0:29:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,These are stages, but it's not causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.33,0:29:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the whole theory of evolution is incorrect.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.33,0:29:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolution has to do with A, B, and C.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.55,0:29:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolution occurs in consciousness and then expresses itself downward.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.92,0:29:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll get into causality later.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.51,0:29:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.51,0:29:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So consciousness is everywhere present.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.51,0:29:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say like a radio wave.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.03,0:29:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So anybody within that field would give us the same answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.28,0:29:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The question does not go in this direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.50,0:30:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We think the questions and answers go from person to person,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.33,0:30:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,by their telephone, by their computer, or by asking them just like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.33,0:30:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What actually happens is the statement or the image or whatever is held in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.50,0:30:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and it goes to consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.50,0:30:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness then radiates it back to the other person.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.75,0:30:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no communication across this way at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.00,0:30:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,any more than there is causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.00,0:30:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If I hold an image in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.00,0:30:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have to even tell you what that image is.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.31,0:30:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I can test you with kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.31,0:30:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you're connected to this consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.31,0:30:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you will give me the response without even knowing what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.31,0:30:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.67,0:30:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So if I call somebody in a foreign land,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.66,0:30:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,or the other side of the United States,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.03,0:30:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and I have two people there ready to test each other with kinesiology,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.03,0:30:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and I say I'm holding something in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.07,0:30:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the energy of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.29,0:31:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,They will give me a response because of this,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.45,0:31:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,not because of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.45,0:31:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be because of this,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.45,0:31:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,because they don't know what I'm holding in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.45,0:31:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's try it as an experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.79,0:31:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to just do that right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.79,0:31:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.58,0:31:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Number six.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.58,0:31:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,These new triangle things, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.40,0:31:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to hold something in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.40,0:31:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and I want you to test...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.40,0:31:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that guy that started the...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.94,0:31:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah, Page. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.35,0:31:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,A fellow there by the name of Page,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.35,0:31:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm going to hold something in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.20,0:31:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and I want you to test out the energy of the image I'm holding in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.22,0:31:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The image of what I'm holding in mind is positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.30,0:32:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you get?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.79,0:32:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that a true statement?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.03,0:32:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.67,0:32:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to hold another image in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.33,0:32:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to test that image.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.49,0:32:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you get?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.49,0:32:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.34,0:32:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.61,0:32:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Make a statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.61,0:32:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Make a statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.51,0:32:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The image that Doc is holding in mind is positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.51,0:32:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.59,0:32:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And then just tell him to resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.98,0:33:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you get?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.64,0:33:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.07,0:33:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm holding an image in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.55,0:33:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The image that I'm holding in mind is...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.83,0:33:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to say it's positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.09,0:33:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Check out the truth of the statement I just made.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.09,0:33:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.31,0:33:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Adolf Hitler, so I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.63,0:33:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The first image I gave you was Lincoln, positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.63,0:33:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitler, negative.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.88,0:34:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Any questions you want to ask as long as we're on the phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.24,0:34:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm holding a substance in front of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.03,0:34:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.03,0:34:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy of what I'm holding is positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.63,0:34:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Just make that statement to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.07,0:34:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and then test him.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.07,0:34:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Just tell him to resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.55,0:34:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.00,0:34:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.00,0:34:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The image of what I'm holding in my hand now is positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.11,0:34:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Check that statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.90,0:34:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,See if that's a true or false statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.90,0:34:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a true statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.07,0:35:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not a true statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.00,0:35:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.19,0:35:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just explaining on the blackboard here
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.28,0:35:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that consciousness, you know, has no dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.28,0:35:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see, the way it works,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.30,0:35:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think I've ever explained it to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.30,0:35:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is when I hold an image,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.30,0:35:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,it goes into the field of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.30,0:35:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Then when you test him,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.84,0:35:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,he's connected to the same field of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.07,0:35:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,so he tests out.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.07,0:35:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.80,0:35:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it's like my thought goes into the water,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.80,0:35:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and then he gets the thought out of the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.80,0:35:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But the thought doesn't go between me and him,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.80,0:35:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.80,0:35:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I'll get to explain that later.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.15,0:35:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, thanks a lot for cooperating with this little experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.15,0:35:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.15,0:35:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, that was just a fun thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.32,0:35:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,really just to demonstrate
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.51,0:35:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the basic theory, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.51,0:35:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with causality
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.71,0:35:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and various interesting things.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.84,0:36:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's a general theory,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.61,0:36:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,a general theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.57,0:36:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to demonstrate a few of the things that happen
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.86,0:36:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,as a consequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.86,0:36:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,In the book, I talk about critical factor analysis.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.86,0:36:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, if we focus in
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.96,0:36:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,on a specific project,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.28,0:36:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,we don't necessarily have to do anything in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.28,0:36:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to make it happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.78,0:36:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a basic principle, isn't it,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.78,0:36:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,in spiritual teaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.78,0:36:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What you hold in mind tends to materialize,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.78,0:36:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to actualize.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.78,0:36:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's ask that question.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.17,0:36:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What you hold in mind tends to actualize.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.94,0:36:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.94,0:36:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the people who hold negativity in their minds
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.94,0:36:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,tend to experience a life of negativity.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.94,0:36:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a section of a small town
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.32,0:36:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,not far from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.32,0:36:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody who lives there
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.80,0:36:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,has the same kind of a life story.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.80,0:37:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything goes wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.80,0:37:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything goes wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.80,0:37:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is always breaking down.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.80,0:37:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They have all kinds of warrants.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.80,0:37:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They're always in trouble with the law.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.59,0:37:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Their fences don't hold up.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.59,0:37:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Their dogs wander off and bite people.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.59,0:37:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's just one endless negativity after another
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.59,0:37:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,because in this world, that's what happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.59,0:37:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is negativity.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.63,0:37:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Other people will tell you that everything happens
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.63,0:37:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,by synchronicity.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.92,0:37:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as they think bobby pin, they open the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.92,0:37:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in fact, they're not even thinking it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.92,0:37:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The thought comes up, somebody says,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.92,0:37:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,what about a bobby pin?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.92,0:37:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You open the door and your hand is on a bobby pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.92,0:37:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's synchronicity.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.32,0:37:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.32,0:37:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to save time,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.73,0:37:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to save time,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.84,0:37:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you see, all you have to do is hold the thing up here
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.84,0:37:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,because to actualize it
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.84,0:37:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,can be quite a formidable undertaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.86,0:37:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,When we talked about causality,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.86,0:37:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,we said things do not operate ABC.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.88,0:38:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The Empire State Building was held
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.88,0:38:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in mind by the consciousness of its creator.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.76,0:38:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That then manifested in this direction
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.76,0:38:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and manifested out in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.42,0:38:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's take a few pet projects I've had over the years
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.42,0:38:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and didn't have time to actually do anything about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.42,0:38:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It always annoyed me when I was setting the VCR
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.86,0:38:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that when you run a TV station,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.86,0:38:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,when you run through the stations,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.86,0:38:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,there's nothing that identifies the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.96,0:38:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the only way you could tell what number you're setting it on
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.44,0:38:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,would be to look at the TV guide, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.21,0:38:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I always thought, wouldn't it be neat
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.21,0:38:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,if these stations would put a little logo
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.21,0:38:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,in the lower right-hand corner
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.21,0:38:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,or the lower left-hand corner?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.36,0:38:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't they have a little logo going there
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.36,0:38:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what the program is?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.36,0:38:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,24 hours a day, they should have their logo there.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.36,0:38:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And to make it even better,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.36,0:38:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,they could have the time and the temperature,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.36,0:38:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, little figures under there or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.69,0:38:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when I'm going to set my VCR
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.69,0:39:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm looking for Channel 5,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.69,0:39:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,why do I have to look up that there's a cowboy program
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.69,0:39:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and run through all the programs
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.69,0:39:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to find a cowboy program
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.69,0:39:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and hope that's Channel 5?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.69,0:39:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't they just have 5 in the lower hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.17,0:39:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I never had a chance to do anything about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.17,0:39:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but I held it in mind rather strongly
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.17,0:39:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,for a couple of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.42,0:39:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the logo suddenly appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.42,0:39:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They've never had a logo appear
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.42,0:39:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in the lower corner of any TV station.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.42,0:39:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You had to wait till the station break,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.84,0:39:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,usually on the hour,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.84,0:39:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and then a big 5 would appear, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.92,0:39:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They wouldn't even give you the station
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.92,0:39:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,on the half hour most of the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.92,0:39:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,A very big annoyance.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.92,0:39:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I just held that in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.05,0:39:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,how nice that would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.05,0:39:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, in fact,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.05,0:39:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,all the channels have their little logo there.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.05,0:39:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm working to perfect it
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.05,0:39:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,by holding the time and the temperature strongly.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.05,0:39:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's just ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.44,0:39:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Those logos appearing in the TV stations
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.44,0:39:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,would have appeared
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.71,0:40:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,even if I didn't hold that in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.71,0:40:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it wouldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.46,0:40:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,My strongly holding it in mind is desirable
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.46,0:40:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and sort of sending it out
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.46,0:40:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is what was responsible for its appearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.46,0:40:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.51,0:40:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.51,0:40:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,People deny the strength of their own mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.63,0:40:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We all live in the world of our own creation,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.63,0:40:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of our own perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.63,0:40:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, here is another pet project
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.63,0:40:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I had going on for quite a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.63,0:40:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And again, I didn't have much time to handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.59,0:40:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But the dominance of gangs of the inner city,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.82,0:40:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw there was only one way,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.88,0:40:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,through critical factor analysis,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.88,0:40:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,which I talk about in the book,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.88,0:40:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,a very complex problem
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.88,0:40:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,has within it exactly one point.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.07,0:40:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you put your finger on that one point,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.07,0:40:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,so a giant clock works,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.07,0:40:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you can stop a giant clock works,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.07,0:40:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,as complex as it looks,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.07,0:40:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,if you know where to put your finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.07,0:40:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's take street crime and the gangs.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.96,0:40:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The most crucial of all the gangs
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.96,0:41:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,was the Gangster Disciples of Chicago
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.96,0:41:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,because they were politically organizing into PACs
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.96,0:41:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and beginning to elect people to the city council.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.67,0:41:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Huge incomes of $100 million a day in drugs,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.67,0:41:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,dominating.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.38,0:41:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So what I saw was that only by using RICO,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.51,0:41:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,conspiracy law,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.51,0:41:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,could you stop the gangs.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.21,0:41:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So one member of a gang commits a crime,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.21,0:41:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you then arrest the whole gang for conspiracy
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.23,0:41:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,because I've treated a lot of gang members
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.23,0:41:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and I know that everything that that gang is planning
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.23,0:41:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is known by everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.23,0:41:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's really, they're all in consort.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.75,0:41:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So I sent out a letter
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.78,0:41:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to everybody from Janet Reno
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.78,0:41:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to the federal judiciary,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.78,0:41:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the state judiciary,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.78,0:41:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the governors of the states,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.03,0:41:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,prosecutors, district attorneys,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.44,0:41:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and it turned out to be quite a formidable task.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.21,0:42:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought, well, I'll just concentrate on Cook County
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.21,0:42:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's where the focus,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.21,0:42:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the fulcrum of all this is the United States
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.21,0:42:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,because the Gangster Disciples were spreading
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.21,0:42:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and becoming the largest gang in the United States
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.21,0:42:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and coalescing with the gangs
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.21,0:42:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,in all the major cities in the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.21,0:42:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So I began to image this as critical
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.40,0:42:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that RICO was the way to stop the gangs
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.67,0:42:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and specifically the Chicago Gangster Disciples,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.67,0:42:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,which is run by a very politically brilliant murderer
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.23,0:42:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,currently in Joliet prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.55,0:42:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Up to now, nothing has effectively stopped the gangs.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.55,0:42:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They pretty much rule the big cities,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.55,0:42:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,have taken over the big cities,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.55,0:42:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,destroyed its economy, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.55,0:42:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So I began to image using RICO
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.98,0:42:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,all right, this last week,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.19,0:42:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it suddenly appears in the paper,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.40,0:42:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,two weeks ago, January 29th, 1996,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.40,0:43:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Arizona Republic.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.40,0:43:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Trial begins today for a gang
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.84,0:43:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that may be the largest in the U.S.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.84,0:43:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and what they're being caught on is conspiracy.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.84,0:43:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, let's ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.36,0:43:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Holding in mind that RICO was the critical factor
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.26,0:43:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to stop the gangs
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.26,0:43:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is what brought about today,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.65,0:43:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,was manifested as that headline.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.11,0:43:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.11,0:43:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And yes, my holding in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.23,0:43:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,on the specific point
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.23,0:43:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and zeroing in and sending out letters
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.23,0:43:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to critical people,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.50,0:43:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,almost everybody answered except Janet Reno.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.19,0:43:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet Reno was glad to get my letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.19,0:43:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.19,0:43:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Janet Reno was not glad to ever get my letter
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.19,0:43:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,because she never replied.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.19,0:43:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if anybody else paid any attention,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.19,0:43:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's not even important.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.19,0:43:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't the sending out the letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.48,0:43:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's ask that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.48,0:43:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I never asked that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.71,0:44:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Was sending out the letters critical
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.71,0:44:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to this resolution of an impossible problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.71,0:44:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.71,0:44:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.71,0:44:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasted my time sending out the letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.03,0:44:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So sometimes we can, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.03,0:44:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,put some effort into it in manifest world,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.03,0:44:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but generally speaking,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.07,0:44:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the holding in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.07,0:44:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There was something else I did years and years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.07,0:44:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,when I first noticed this phenomenon.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.21,0:44:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sort of into unicorn cards,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.21,0:44:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and I looked all over,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.80,0:44:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can hardly ever find a unicorn card anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.80,0:44:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So I began to desire and image unicorn cards
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.23,0:44:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and how great it would be if they were everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.23,0:44:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Then unicorn cards appeared everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.40,0:44:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Did holding that unicorn in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.40,0:44:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,make those cards manifest?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.40,0:44:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.40,0:44:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, sure did.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.40,0:44:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The same with Expresso.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.40,0:44:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Expresso was very hard to find in the United States,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.40,0:44:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,almost anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.40,0:44:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So I held in mind how great it would be
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.40,0:44:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,if Expresso was everywhere available.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.40,0:45:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you can get it in the fast food stores.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.40,0:45:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,With holding in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.40,0:45:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Expresso is partially responsible
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.75,0:45:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,for its manifesting as widespread availability.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.88,0:45:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.88,0:45:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.88,0:45:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see, what you hold in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.88,0:45:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to manifest if it's for the good of mankind,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.13,0:45:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and you just keep holding it in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.13,0:45:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody knows this who's ever done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.13,0:45:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Every place I've ever lived,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.13,0:45:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,including this place,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.13,0:45:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,was imaged first.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.13,0:45:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a small little remote place
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.13,0:45:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,next to a creek,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.71,0:45:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in an arid place like Arizona,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.71,0:45:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the big place I had back east,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.71,0:45:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,was again imaged in the woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.71,0:45:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we hold in mind tends to manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.21,0:45:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a very, very critical thing to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.63,0:45:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We said that 85% of the people on the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.73,0:45:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.73,0:45:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's so.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.13,0:46:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,85% of the people on the planet calibrate below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.13,0:46:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.50,0:46:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,0.4% of the people calibrate 500 or over.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.50,0:46:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.50,0:46:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that would sound quite alarming, wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.71,0:46:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,85% of the people on the planet live here.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.92,0:46:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,As far as 500 and up on additional love,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.92,0:46:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,0.4% of the population.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.92,0:46:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So why doesn't the world destroy itself?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.44,0:46:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the power of the thought here
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.01,0:46:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is so enormously powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.01,0:46:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that one person holding one loving thought at this level
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.01,0:46:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,totally counterbalances maybe 50,000 people
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.30,0:46:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,holding negative thoughts in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.00,0:46:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So most of us think all kinds of negative thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.67,0:46:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.67,0:46:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This little fear, that little fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.67,0:46:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,this little resentment or anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.67,0:46:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And it doesn't destroy us
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.19,0:46:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,because we also have a loving thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.19,0:46:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We also have a loving thought about our pets,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.53,0:47:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,about our friends or parents or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.05,0:47:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So one loving thought from this level up here
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.05,0:47:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,is so powerful that it prevents all these negative thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.05,0:47:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have throughout the day from actually destroying us.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.05,0:47:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get what the consciousness level of mankind is right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.69,0:47:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness level, let's get it in history.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.69,0:47:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness level of mankind in the year 1900
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.69,0:47:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,was over 200, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.61,0:47:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,In the year 1800, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.61,0:47:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness level of mankind in the year 1700
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.19,0:47:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,was 190, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.69,0:47:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness level of mankind in the year 1000
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.69,0:47:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,was 190, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.98,0:47:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness level of mankind stayed at 190
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.98,0:47:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,for all the centuries until 1986, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.23,0:47:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, in 1985, the consciousness level of mankind was over 200 resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.38,0:47:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1986, the consciousness level of mankind was 200, over 200 resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.42,0:48:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Before we leave this brief discussion of consciousness as a subject,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.55,0:48:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to say a little bit more about the map of consciousness and about causality
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.03,0:48:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and relate a little bit more closely to the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.92,0:48:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In the book, it's quite obvious that positions from 200 and up are positions of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.94,0:48:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Positions of 200 and down are positions of force.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.88,0:48:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What makes the difference is, for one thing, motive, intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.28,0:48:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What is your primary goal? What are your highest values?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.63,0:48:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the basic law that you live by when the chips are down?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.90,0:48:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And these are levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.03,0:48:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The lower levels are really levels of victimhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.75,0:48:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They all come about by virtue of positionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.84,0:49:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,As you take a position, you see, you limit your perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.00,0:49:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are all levels of perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.09,0:49:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,These are very limited levels of perception in which you scope in on a very, very small piece of reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.03,0:49:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you live from a higher view of, let's say, identifying with the good of mankind,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.88,0:49:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you end up towards the top of the calibrated scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.55,0:49:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's see what we mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.09,0:49:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say an unfortunate incident happens to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.03,0:49:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say you lose some money or you make a deal and somebody doesn't pay you the money back, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.07,0:49:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you could adopt any one of these positions, you see, depending on what your priority in life would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.55,0:49:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be ashamed of the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.76,0:49:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You can not bring it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.42,0:49:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You can feel hopeless about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.38,0:49:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You can feel guilty and berate yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.71,0:50:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You can feel apathetic that it's hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.84,0:50:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to be done about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.01,0:50:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You can go into grief and wail about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.86,0:50:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Ours is a crybaby society.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.71,0:50:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody likes to go into these victim roles.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.76,0:50:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You can get angry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.07,0:50:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You can get indignant.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.96,0:50:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody talks about rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.30,0:50:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.57,0:50:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It falls in here somewhere, you know, having to do with anger and pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.40,0:50:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my right to do something or other.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.46,0:50:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,See, right has is a rather limited perception because you can look at the same event from the position of responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.69,0:50:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Responsibility is way up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.26,0:50:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,To a person who's responsible, right is just part of the picture and usually sort of an irrelevant part of the picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.13,0:50:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not concerned with rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.01,0:51:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Down below, people are preoccupied with right and wrong, with morality, with good and bad, and classifying things in those categories.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.50,0:51:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Courage, for the first time, is the capacity to look at both sides of the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.13,0:51:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So a person might be, down here, might be indignant.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.00,0:51:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,A person might be into rage, say, let's sue them.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.09,0:51:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A person might be arrogant about the whole thing or fall into denial.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.59,0:51:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.44,0:51:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to look at both the upside and the downside.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.34,0:51:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything has a consequence and you may decide either to act or not act.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.13,0:51:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Neutral is a position of, sort of, it's okay if you take action.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.44,0:51:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay if you don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.59,0:51:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really not all that important.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.61,0:51:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Willingness is willingness to look at it from a higher and a broader viewpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.80,0:51:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Acceptance might be that that's the nature of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.48,0:51:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Reason might be taking the intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.30,0:52:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The intelligent view of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.84,0:52:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,One's love for one's fellow human being may preclude taking any action.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.40,0:52:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say somebody takes a piece of your property and wrecks it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.53,0:52:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This has happened to me in the not-too-distant future.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.46,0:52:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,A past, rather.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.09,0:52:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was quite a sizable loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.01,0:52:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I could have gone into any one of these positions here, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.71,0:52:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I happen to know that the person has no money whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.57,0:52:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So, frankly, I didn't even see...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.21,0:52:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't see the point of bringing it up with the person, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.21,0:52:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you could say it's my right.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.21,0:52:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I could have taken a position that is hopeless to bring it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.21,0:52:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I could have gotten arrogant about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.28,0:52:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I could have gotten angry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.28,0:52:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But the real thing is I love that person and I knew that if I brought this up to that person's awareness,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.34,0:52:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,they would have gone into guilt and shame about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.34,0:53:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you really love somebody, if they can't do anything about a situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.71,0:53:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,there's really no point to bringing it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.92,0:53:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you would be throwing them into the bottom of the box here,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.92,0:53:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,where they're going to feel guilt and shame about something which is already past.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.92,0:53:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't do anything about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.92,0:53:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And they don't have the assets to correct it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.92,0:53:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.28,0:53:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the loving thing to do would be, in this particular instance, just overlook it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.28,0:53:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And accepting that that's the way life goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.28,0:53:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't drive your car, you know, 10,000, 20,000 miles a year without sooner or later getting a dent in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.28,0:53:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, those are the things, the wear and tear of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.28,0:53:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Taking that position keeps a person sort of in a state of joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.55,0:53:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the joy there?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.55,0:53:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The joy is that one is no longer at the effect of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.55,0:53:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,From 200 down, one is the victim of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.01,0:53:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Because happiness is out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.01,0:53:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness is out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.19,0:54:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,These are levels, let's say, of revenge and getting even, of jealousy, possessiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.19,0:54:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If you get the job, so and so.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.63,0:54:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If you get the job, so one's self-esteem, one's level of being is dependent on consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.48,0:54:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It depends on how a thing turns out.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.48,0:54:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If you get the job, don't get the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.48,0:54:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You get the money, you don't get the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.48,0:54:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You get the girl, you don't get the girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.63,0:54:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, one is the victim of consequences in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.84,0:54:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,As we see from causality, as we get, we'll talk a little bit more about that before we leave this subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.94,0:54:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What determines an external event is millions and millions of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.94,0:54:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it takes the entire universe to bring about a certain consequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.51,0:54:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,To be at the effect of that, to be the victim of that, then, is to be like a leaf thrown about in the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.51,0:54:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And we know lots of people whose emotions, from hour to hour, day to day, week to week, month to month,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.51,0:55:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,are buffeted about by the arrows of fortune and fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.55,0:55:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If things go well, they're up. If things are down, they're not.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.65,0:55:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So, from 200 and up, you begin to transcend the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.65,0:55:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And from about 350 on up, you begin to re-own your power.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.13,0:55:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,These positions down here are those of powerlessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.13,0:55:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Because what happens to you is what goes on out in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.13,0:55:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You've projected your own power into the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.19,0:55:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you get to about 350, which is acceptance, you begin to own that you yourself are the source of your own happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.19,0:55:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I gave an example in the book of all these different ways of responding to finding yourself in jail, let's say.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.17,0:55:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You can hang yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.36,0:55:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You can become very spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.36,0:55:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You can join a 12-step group and become quite enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.65,0:55:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You can become very intelligent.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.65,0:56:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You can go to the law library and earn a degree.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.61,0:56:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,There are all kinds of different ways we can handle the same circumstance,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.61,0:56:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,depending on what your overall motivation towards life is.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.61,0:56:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So, these are levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.88,0:56:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,These are levels of very limited perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.88,0:56:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,These are also levels of selfishness and egocentricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.88,0:56:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all levels of me, me, me.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.88,0:56:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the beginning of the levels of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.88,0:56:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And these are the levels up here of really the good of all mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.38,0:56:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What will the impact of my actions be on humanity as a whole?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.09,0:56:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people who have had a hard time in our society,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.09,0:56:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,have had it because they were acting, let's say, from the good of all mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.09,0:56:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Linus Pauling, who I knew, he and I had done a book together back in the 70s.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.21,0:56:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He won the Nobel Prize twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.59,0:56:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Once for chemistry and once for peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.46,0:56:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,When he stood alone in front of the White House,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.46,0:57:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it was in the middle of the McCarthy era,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.92,0:57:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and he stood against nuclear testing
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.13,0:57:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,because the nuclear fallout, the radioactive fallout,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.13,0:57:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,had a deleterious effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.13,0:57:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Not all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.13,0:57:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He wasn't interested in any of these lower levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.36,0:57:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to go back to consciousness itself a little bit again.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.03,0:57:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure we understand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.36,0:57:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to go back to causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.36,0:57:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We said within the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.34,0:57:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the Newtonian paradigm of reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.63,0:57:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Newton defined for us a four-dimensional world,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.86,0:57:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the world of the computer, of mathematics and science.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.40,0:57:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It calibrates in the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.69,0:57:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Newton himself calibrates at 499, as does Einstein.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.69,0:57:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the level of reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.98,0:57:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes you up to this level here.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.98,0:58:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,For some reason, all the greatest scientists who have ever lived calibrate around 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.98,0:58:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the world of science in which A causes B causes C.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.88,0:58:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, when we go beyond that level of awareness,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.86,0:58:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you see, that's a limited perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.86,0:58:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,A limited perception of awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.86,0:58:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,As we get into the higher 400s,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.86,0:58:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,we start becoming aware of chaos theory,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.86,0:58:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,non-linear dynamics, fuzzy logic, set theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.86,0:58:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,As we get to the high 400s,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.86,0:58:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,we get to a level such as the advanced theoretical physics,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.86,0:58:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,quantum mechanics as described, let's say, by David Bohm.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.19,0:58:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Bohm, his thinking, etc.,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.19,0:58:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is right on the level of,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.19,0:58:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say, beyond 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.19,0:58:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He's already into the 500s.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.19,0:58:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He has become aware of the difference in causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.15,0:58:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,How does cause work?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.15,0:58:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, within the visible world,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.15,0:59:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the manifest material world as we see it,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.15,0:59:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.34,0:59:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a shocking shift of paradigm
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.36,0:59:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,when you hear it for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.36,0:59:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We're so used to thinking that A causes B causes C,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.36,0:59:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,like a set of billiard balls hitting each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.03,0:59:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes sort of a jump of paradigm
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.03,0:59:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to realize that none of that is happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.80,0:59:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,As I showed you when I was going like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.80,0:59:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to show you an example of how a flower develops,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.88,0:59:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the cause is not within the manifest world.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.88,0:59:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say that cause originates in consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.67,0:59:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that this sequence ABC
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.92,0:59:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is held as a concept in consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.50,0:59:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This ABC, now,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.50,0:59:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,has the power to manifest sequentially
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.53,0:59:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,as this series ABC.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.53,1:00:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Cause proceeds from unlimited high power
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.01,1:00:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to lesser and lesser power into the material world,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.01,1:00:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,like a step-down transformer.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.80,1:00:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness and beyond consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.80,1:00:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,there is that which is called awareness.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.96,1:00:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll get back to this
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.96,1:00:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,when we get to the spiritual aspects later in the course.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.23,1:00:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Awareness, then, is beyond consciousness even.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.23,1:00:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness is potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.76,1:00:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with is and is not,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.76,1:00:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,beingness and non-beingness,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.76,1:00:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,existence and non-existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.76,1:00:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Awareness is beyond all of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.09,1:00:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The highest power, then, is that of awareness,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.25,1:00:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,which is infinite, always was, always will be,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.34,1:00:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.59,1:00:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Within consciousness, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.59,1:00:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,arises the beginnings of form
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.59,1:00:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,on the level of essence.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.80,1:00:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we might say this is more the level of essence.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.80,1:01:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Essence, when run through the transformer
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.46,1:01:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of the human consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.48,1:01:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,comes down through desire and tension
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.48,1:01:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and manifests within the visible world.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.03,1:01:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,When we see a sequence of billiard balls,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.03,1:01:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,such as ABC,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.03,1:01:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,what we're seeing is
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.03,1:01:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the causality manifesting
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.32,1:01:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,as this,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.32,1:01:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and these are preconditions.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.38,1:01:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,These are conditions.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.38,1:01:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The condition of B appearing in this series,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.63,1:01:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,A is a condition to it,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.19,1:01:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,but it is not a cause of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.19,1:01:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So that when we talk about
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.63,1:01:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,a flower, let's say,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.63,1:01:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the flower here,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.69,1:01:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,he's this big a flower,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.69,1:01:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and now, a month later, he's this big a flower,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.69,1:01:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and now it's this big a flower,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.76,1:01:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.84,1:01:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Newtonian concept,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.84,1:01:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,this causes this,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.84,1:02:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and this causes this,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.84,1:02:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,but from a higher viewpoint,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.92,1:02:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no cause involved.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.65,1:02:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,These are both consequences
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.90,1:02:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of this M field, you might call it,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.84,1:02:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,morphogenetic field.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.84,1:02:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolution, if we check it out with kinesiology,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.61,1:02:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll see this is so.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.61,1:02:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolution takes place on the level of
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.57,1:02:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,morphogenetic fields.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.57,1:02:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That is like a pattern
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.57,1:02:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,held within consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.57,1:02:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,which then manifests out as its physical expression.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.73,1:02:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolution does not take place
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.73,1:02:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,within the physical world.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.80,1:02:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the tiger with the biggest jaws survives
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.80,1:02:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,because he can eat more and kill more.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.80,1:02:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the theory.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.80,1:02:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, that's not how it happens at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.11,1:02:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This is necessary to understand
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.11,1:03:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,if you realize that what we hold in consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.65,1:03:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to manifest.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.88,1:03:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're holding something up here,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.88,1:03:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it's going to tend to manifest,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.88,1:03:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,materialize,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.88,1:03:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and appear within the physical world.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.13,1:03:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You can experiment with that
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.13,1:03:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and prove that to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.13,1:03:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Pick something that you desire
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.13,1:03:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that would be good for life,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.13,1:03:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,good for mankind,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.13,1:03:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and just keep picturing it,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.13,1:03:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,holding it in mind,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.13,1:03:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,desiring it,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.13,1:03:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe draw it,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.13,1:03:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe even write letters to people.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.13,1:03:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you mail them or don't mail them,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.13,1:03:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,apparently makes no difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.13,1:03:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So the best thing to do is,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.13,1:03:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,if you picture
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.13,1:03:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that the way to keep animals from getting lost
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.51,1:03:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is by having some kind of a little radio transmitter,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.51,1:03:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody obviously held that in mind
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.51,1:03:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,because now you can buy them in the marketplace.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.51,1:03:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you have a pet project
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.51,1:03:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you would like to work on
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.51,1:03:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,for your own sake
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.51,1:03:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,because the mind tends to be skeptical
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.51,1:03:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,about such things,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.51,1:04:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,put it down in a notebook.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.57,1:04:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Put it down in a notebook
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.57,1:04:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and then just wait for it to show up
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.57,1:04:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,within the visible world.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.57,1:04:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.63,1:04:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,mention before we leave
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.63,1:04:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the subject of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.63,1:04:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that these numbers that are on here
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.63,1:04:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,are logarithms.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.63,1:04:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,These are logarithms
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.63,1:04:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and the direction of the arrow indicates
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.63,1:04:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,whether this makes you weak
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.63,1:04:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,or it makes you strong.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.61,1:04:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What makes the difference
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.67,1:04:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,with these levels
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.67,1:04:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you might call
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.67,1:04:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,a person's level of vested interest.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.03,1:04:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,People say,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.07,1:04:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,well what sets my consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.07,1:04:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,or somebody else's consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.07,1:04:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,where it is?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.23,1:04:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's what you have a vested interest in.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.57,1:04:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So if people have a vested interest
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.57,1:04:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say at the level of pride
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.57,1:04:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,they can blow up innocent women and children
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.71,1:04:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's a negative energy
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.71,1:04:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in the name of the IRA, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.71,1:04:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They can wave the flag
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.71,1:04:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and say it's patriotism
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.71,1:04:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,but actually it's just arrogance
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.71,1:04:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're placing
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.71,1:05:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,their own political viewpoint
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.71,1:05:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,above the lives of innocent citizens.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.76,1:05:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So what it is you're willing to die for,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.76,1:05:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,your vested,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.76,1:05:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,what you have a vested interest in.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.76,1:05:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,These people here have a vested interest
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.76,1:05:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in being right at any cost,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.76,1:05:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,being right.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.76,1:05:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's their vested interest.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.69,1:05:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So they're willing to sacrifice love,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.69,1:05:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,marriages, joy, positions, jobs
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.69,1:05:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,for being right, being right.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.84,1:05:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's where you set your power
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.01,1:05:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is what you're willing to go for.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.09,1:05:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And I wanted to recalibrate
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.09,1:05:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the power of an individual thought
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.09,1:05:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,which has never been done
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.09,1:05:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,as far as I know ever.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.09,1:05:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just try it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.09,1:05:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And a thought at the energy level of 100,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.90,1:05:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,energy level 100,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.15,1:05:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,because most people have lots and lots
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.15,1:05:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of fearful thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.80,1:06:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of that thought is between
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.28,1:06:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,10 to the minus 700
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.40,1:06:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and 10 to the minus 800 million
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.30,1:06:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,microwatts resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.30,1:06:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,At the level of 100
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.76,1:06:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,a thought is more powerful
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.76,1:06:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,than 1 to the minus the log
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.92,1:06:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,minus 10 to the minus 700 million resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.92,1:06:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.67,1:06:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's take a thought
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.67,1:06:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,at the level of love, 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.34,1:06:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,A thought at the level of love
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.34,1:06:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,measures 10 to the minus approximately
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.78,1:06:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,35 million microwatts resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.78,1:06:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So the difference between
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.23,1:06:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,10 to the minus 35 million microwatts
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.25,1:06:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and 10 to the minus
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.48,1:06:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,700 million microwatts,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.48,1:06:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the difference in power is so enormous
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.48,1:06:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it's really beyond comprehension.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.48,1:06:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But the significance is
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.76,1:07:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that a loving thought is so powerful
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.76,1:07:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that it contradicts thousands
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.76,1:07:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and thousands of negative thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.76,1:07:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And if it weren't for that,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.76,1:07:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,then salvation would not be possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.76,1:07:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we've got Lydia here today,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.21,1:07:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,very fortunate.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.21,1:07:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, David.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.21,1:07:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And she's been part of a research team
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.21,1:07:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,for NBC
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.21,1:07:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that did a very famous documentary
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.21,1:07:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,on PBS on the Sphinx
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.59,1:07:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and having to do with
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.42,1:07:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the age of the Sphinx
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.42,1:07:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and various other things.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.42,1:07:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you tell us
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.42,1:07:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,what you've been up to?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.42,1:07:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'd be happy to.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.42,1:07:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, you got that...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.42,1:07:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the research you did won the Emmy Award,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.42,1:07:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand, for research.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.92,1:07:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we did.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.92,1:07:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, a colleague of ours,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.92,1:07:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. John West,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.92,1:07:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,spent many, many years
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.92,1:07:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,on the hypothesis
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.92,1:07:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that the Sphinx was older
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.92,1:07:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,than anything else
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.92,1:07:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,on the Giza Plateau.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.92,1:07:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And he based his assumption
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.92,1:07:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,on the fact that
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.92,1:08:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it's weathered by water.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.92,1:08:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We finally have hard science
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.92,1:08:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,available to us in this century
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.92,1:08:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to go and test his theory
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.92,1:08:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and prove it out,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.92,1:08:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,which is something we did in 1993.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.92,1:08:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,When we were at the Giza Plateau,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.92,1:08:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we happened to have
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.92,1:08:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. DeBecke
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.92,1:08:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Colorado School of Mines
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.93,1:08:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,use his new infrared photography methods
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.93,1:08:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and his current
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.93,1:08:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,sonography methods
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.93,1:08:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to test what was under
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.11,1:08:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the Sphinx in the plateau.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.11,1:08:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And we found three man-made chambers
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.11,1:08:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,under the Sphinx.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.11,1:08:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what this did for us
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.11,1:08:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,was pose the question
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.11,1:08:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,for the public at large,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.11,1:08:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,how did they get there?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.11,1:08:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Who put them there?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.11,1:08:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,How old are they?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.11,1:08:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,How long have they been there?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.11,1:08:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we can get into them,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.11,1:08:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,since no one we know of
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.11,1:08:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in mankind's history
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.11,1:08:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,has ever set foot there,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.11,1:08:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,what's there?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.11,1:08:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Who put it there?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.63,1:08:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to know answers
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.63,1:08:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to all these questions.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.63,1:08:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Possibly this technique,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.63,1:08:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hawkins can give us
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.63,1:08:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,a place to begin.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.63,1:09:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn't that
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.63,1:09:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Perry Casey's...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.63,1:09:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Edgar Cayce,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.63,1:09:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the sleeping prophet
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.63,1:09:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,from about 50 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.63,1:09:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.63,1:09:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,postulated there was
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.63,1:09:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,a man-made chamber
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.19,1:09:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,under the Pala of the Sphinx.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.19,1:09:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,This is one of the things
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.19,1:09:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we went looking for.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.19,1:09:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And now this is
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.19,1:09:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,what science has confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.19,1:09:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.19,1:09:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We found not only
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.19,1:09:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that chamber,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.19,1:09:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,two others.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.19,1:09:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But nobody's been in them yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.19,1:09:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Never.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.19,1:09:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.19,1:09:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.19,1:09:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,there's been
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.19,1:09:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,another chamber
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.19,1:09:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,in what we think of
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.19,1:09:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,as recorded history.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.19,1:09:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.19,1:09:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Never.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.19,1:09:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a first.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.19,1:09:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to go back.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.19,1:09:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.19,1:09:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Great.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.19,1:09:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So you think you might
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.19,1:09:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,go back there shortly?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.19,1:09:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,In March of 96,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.19,1:09:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll begin.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.19,1:09:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.19,1:09:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we won't have
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.19,1:09:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the permission
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.19,1:09:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to go two,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.19,1:09:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,three,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.19,1:09:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,400 feet
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.19,1:09:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,under the plateau
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.19,1:09:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,at this time.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.19,1:09:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But we do have
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.19,1:09:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,specific feelings,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.19,1:09:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,questions.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.19,1:09:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's ask some questions
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.19,1:09:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,with kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.19,1:09:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and see what's there.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.19,1:09:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that'd be
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.19,1:09:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,very valuable for us.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.19,1:09:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.19,1:09:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So the chambers
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.19,1:09:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,are there,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.19,1:09:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,correct?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.19,1:09:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.19,1:09:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Which arm?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.19,1:09:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's try this one.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.81,1:09:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.81,1:10:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Um,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.81,1:10:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,art science says
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.81,1:10:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,there's three chambers
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.81,1:10:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,under what?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.81,1:10:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Under the Sphinx
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.00,1:10:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and under the plateau.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.00,1:10:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Under the plateau.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.77,1:10:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That is true.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.77,1:10:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.77,1:10:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There's more than three.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.23,1:10:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.23,1:10:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody's been
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.23,1:10:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in those chambers
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.23,1:10:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,in recent recorded history.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.97,1:10:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.97,1:10:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,There is,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.97,1:10:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,uh,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.97,1:10:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,valuables
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.84,1:10:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,within those chambers.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.84,1:10:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.84,1:10:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.84,1:10:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There were
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.84,1:10:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,valuables
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.84,1:10:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,within those chambers.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.00,1:10:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we want to...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.00,1:10:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What more do you need
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.00,1:10:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to know now?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.00,1:10:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.00,1:10:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.00,1:10:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What would be useful
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.00,1:10:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,then?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.00,1:10:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I speculate that,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.00,1:10:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,yes,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.00,1:10:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,those chambers
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.00,1:10:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,have been entered,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.00,1:10:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but with your typical
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.00,1:10:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Egyptian grave robbing,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.00,1:10:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I really believe
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.00,1:10:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the people,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.00,1:10:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the locals,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.00,1:10:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,know all about
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.00,1:10:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,what's immediately
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.40,1:10:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,under the surface
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.40,1:10:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,in the plateau.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.60,1:10:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Um,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.60,1:10:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of psychics
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.80,1:10:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and others
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.80,1:10:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,speculate
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.80,1:10:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a complex
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.80,1:10:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,further below,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.07,1:10:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,another two
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.07,1:10:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,or three hundred feet,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.07,1:10:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,a whole tunnel system
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.07,1:11:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to know
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.07,1:11:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,who built these tunnels?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.07,1:11:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Who built
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.07,1:11:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the original temples?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.07,1:11:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Were they Atlanteans?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.07,1:11:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Were they Babylonians?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.07,1:11:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Were they Sumerians?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.07,1:11:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Were they from
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.07,1:11:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,another planet?
